{"id":37324,"alternative_names":[{"id":29111,"name":"\u30ca\u30a4\u30c8\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30ab\u30fc"}],"cover":{"id":394316,"image_id":"co8g98","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/co8g98.jpg"},"first_release_date":623203200,"genres":[{"id":5,"name":"Shooter"},{"id":33,"name":"Arcade"}],"involved_companies":[{"id":274722,"company":{"id":817,"name":"Taito"},"developer":true,"publisher":true}],"name":"Night Striker","release_dates":[{"id":613925,"date":623203200,"human":"Oct 1989","platform":{"id":52,"name":"Arcade"},"release_region":{"id":5,"region":"japan"}}],"screenshots":[{"id":688703,"image_id":"sceren","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/sceren.jpg"},{"id":688704,"image_id":"scereo","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/scereo.jpg"},{"id":688705,"image_id":"scerep","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/scerep.jpg"}],"similar_games":[78770,43367,105269,55038,111846,68286,107318,103301,113362,12539],"slug":"night-striker","summary":"Night Striker (\u30ca\u30a4\u30c8\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30ab\u30fc) is an arcade game developed by Taito. It is a futuristic on-the-rails shooter which plays similarly to Sega's Space Harrier, though has you pilot a hover vehicle instead.\n\nThe game was brought to the Sega Mega-CD in 1993, where graphically it was downscaled for the weaker hardware. It was also brought to the Sega Saturn as Night Striker S (\u30ca\u30a4\u30c8\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30ab\u30fc\uff33) in 1996 - essentially the same game, but with an extra \"Saturn Mode\" and a few small enhancements. No versions have ever left Japan.","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/night-striker","videos":[{"id":118342,"video_id":"Reb7nxgOTvQ"}],"websites":[{"id":297731,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Night_Striker","type":{"id":3,"type":"Wikipedia"}}]}